description.narrative: The Government pledged to implement CRC and develop human capital by reducing the percentage of children who are multi-dimensionally deprived according to the national definition by half by 2030. UNICEF-supported evidence generation, including the Lao Social Indicator Survey II (LSIS-II 2017) and the Multiple Overlapping Deprivation Analysis (MODA 2018), has guided the review and development of sectoral plans and strategies, the review of the 8th NSEDP, the development of the 9th NSEDP, and SDG localization. Important progress was made in the improvement of social norms and behaviours relating to child survival and development utilizing C4D practices through a parenting package. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
